  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 12 meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries a required level of 3 but an achieved level of 2. The decision record records Accepted on the basis of compensating evidence from Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, expert judgment from three independent hemolysis modelling groups, and historical precedent from predicate pump studies, none of which formally closes the one-step level shortfall.",
