      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric u_val) applied to hemolysis index at all operating points; metric accounts for experimental and numerical uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "ASME V&V 20 validation metric computed for all 5 operating points. Validation uncertainty u_val ranges 9.1%–14.6%. Model error |E| < u_val at 4 of 5 points; at the fifth point |E| = 18.2% against u_val = 16.8%, within one combined standard uncertainty. Sensitivity analysis confirms this point is not the risk-limiting condition. Level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (hemolysis index) is directly mapped to clinical acceptance criterion; secondary QoIs (shear stress, residence time) are documented as supporting evidence.",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index QoI maps directly to the NIH normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) clinical threshold. Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged shear stress, Lagrangian exposure time) are documented in the analysis plan and used to bound uncertainty in the power-law model. Relevance level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same device geometry at COU operating conditions; fluid analogue properties match within documented tolerance.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (identical to COU geometry) operated at all 5 COU flow-speed combinations with bovine blood at 35% hematocrit. Geometric similarity is exact; fluid analogue deviation is within ±4% viscosity, propagated through UQ. Validation activity relevance level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
