      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria documented; residual targets achieved for all equations; solution independence from initial conditions demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Residual convergence to 1×10⁻⁶ for continuity, momentum, and hemolysis transport equations at all operating points. Three independent initial conditions tested; final solutions agree to within 0.3% on hemolysis index. Solver error level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition application and material property assignment verified against analysis plan.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by a second analyst not involved in model construction. Boundary conditions, material properties, and solver settings verified against the approved analysis plan AP-2023-11. No discrepancies identified. Use error level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selected with documented justification; sensitivity of hemolysis index to model form alternatives quantified.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for confined rotating flows. Giersiepen-Wurzinger and modified Taskin hemolysis models both evaluated; predictions bracket experimental data. Model form sensitivity contributes 11% to total hemolysis index uncertainty, propagated in UQ ensemble. Level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis coefficients α and β) characterised with probability distributions; distributions sourced from peer-reviewed literature or in-house measurement.",
      "rationale": "Six uncertain inputs identified: dynamic viscosity, density, power-law coefficients α and β, red blood cell fragility index, and rotational speed tolerance. Distributions assigned from published literature (n ≥ 15 studies per parameter) and in-house rheometry. Monte Carlo propagation (10,000 samples) performed. Model inputs level 4 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements obtained from at least 3 independent test runs per operating point; inter-run variability reported.",
      "rationale": "Three independent experimental runs conducted per operating point (15 total runs). Inter-run coefficient of variation ranges 4.1%–7.8% across operating points. Pooled experimental uncertainty incorporated into validation metric. Test samples level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that the input parameter space used in validation experiments is equivalent to the COU input parameter space, with formal mapping and documented tolerances for each parameter; any extrapolation beyond the validated range must be bounded by sensitivity analysis at the required level.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments were conducted with bovine blood at 35% hematocrit and 37 °C, which represents the primary operating envelope. Three independent hemolysis modelling groups with a combined 40 years of VAD CFD experience have reviewed the parameter mapping and concur that the input spaces are substantially equivalent. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across the full COU parameter range and the 95th-percentile hemolysis prediction remains 22% below the clinical threshold, providing a comfortable safety margin. Historical data from five predicate centrifugal pump studies show that bovine-blood validation results are consistently conservative relative to clinical human-blood outcomes, further supporting the adequacy of the validation dataset. While a formal parameter-by-parameter equivalency mapping document at the granularity required for level 3 — specifically a documented tolerance band and extrapolation bound for the hematocrit range 30%–40% and the rotational speed range 2,400–3,600 rpm — has not been completed, the team judges that the weight of indirect evidence (expert consensus, UQ margin, historical precedent) is sufficient to support an Accepted decision. The one-step shortfall relative to the required level is acknowledged but considered non-risk-limiting given the 22% margin to the clinical threshold."
    }
